How secure is Uniswap? I‚Äôm terms of Bitcoin being decentralised And always being able to access my funds from my cold wallet.

Uniswap is a decentralized application deployed on Eth mainnet, Polygon, Arbitrum and Optimism. You can swap tokens with the wrapped version of Bitcoin on each respective network but if you are referring buying through FIAT, you will have to find another route.

Another risk besides the impermanent loss is the inventory holding risk. As traditional market makers are exposed to inventory holding risk usually for an extremely short time (say seconds), liquidity providers in Uniswap are exposed to this during their entire duration of the position (say days or months). So this is definitely a risk to consider when providing liquidity.

the terminology is a little confusing, but what is happening is the current ETH chain, which uses PoW, is being upgraded to use PoS. The mechanism of that upgrade is called "The Merge" - because ETH will combine with something called the "Beacon Chain" that has been a testbed/staking environment. https://ethereum.org/en/upgrades/beacon-chain/

Some people do NOT want to participate in this upgrade process. They are proposing (have proposed? will propose)? that they NOT join The Merge and will instead stay on PoW. When a cryptocurrency network splits like this it is called a "Fork".

https://twitter.com/EthereumPoW - this is the group that will run the PoW fork. From their perspective, it is instead the mainline ETH chain that is the fork (calling someone else a fork is another way of saying that they are a "copy" and the ETH PoW is the "true" Ethereum.)
Same lines as with ETH Classic üòÖ

like @La  says, forking of ETH has happened before with EthClassic and its just treated like a separate Layer 1 coin in the crypto ecosystem. 

My expectation is that the EthPow fork tokens will be considered worth much less than Eth, and it may take a while for bridges, CEXes, etc to support those tokens if they ever do at all.
My expectation is that uniswap will disregard/ignore anything to do with the EthPow network and treat it like it doesn't exist. (but im not uniswap...)

The value of the EthPow is only based on the ecosystem around it and what people are willing to trade for it (probably nothing).

1. One side only 2. It needs to be locked in a pool with at least 60 ETH, OR in a pool with at least 60 ETH worth of a another whitelisted asset

what is happening here?
